2 Liquidation Rights. In the event of any liquidation, dissolution or winding up of
the Corporation, the holders of Preferred Stock shall be entitled to receive from the
assets of the Corporation, whether represented by capital, surplus, reserves or earnings,
payment in cash of an amount equal to $100 per share, plus a further amount equal to
unpaid cumulative dividends on Preferred Stock accrued to the date when such payment
shall be made available to the holders thereof, before any distribution of assets shall he
made to the holders of the Common Stock or other shares ranking junior to Preferred
Stock as to the distribution of assets upon liquidation. If, upon such liquidation, disso-
lution or winding up, the assets distributable to the holders of Preferred Stock shall be
insulicient to permit the payment in full to such holders of the preferential amounts to
which they are entitled, then such assets shall be distributed ratably among the shares of
